&lt;h1&gt;ARCHRIVAL CULTURE COLLECTIVE&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Archrival Culture Collective is a national panel of diverse Gen Z consumers who are at the heart of our approach to gathering culturally relevant insights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are always on the lookout for thoughtful, unique perspectives, and we want your voice to be heard!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;WHAT DO COMMUNITY MEMBERS DO?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Archrival Culture Collective, you will receive short surveys and written assignments monthly asking you about the latest trends, habits and behaviors emerging in young consumer culture. Assignments should take no more than 30 minutes to complete, and are always optional.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;HOW WILL MY ANSWERS BE USED BY ARCHRIVAL?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As youth culture experts, Archrival is constantly writing, speaking and sharing what we hear from young people like you. Your insights may appear in our cultural insights publication, &lt;a href=&quot;https://archrival.com/insights&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;ALMANAC&lt;/a&gt;, or in presentations, workshops or strategy brainstorms with major brands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;WILL I BE COMPENSATED?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each month, community members will be entered into a drawing to receive Amazon gift cards and occasional branded swag. While you won’t receive compensation every month, we promise we’ll make it worth it! There will also be opportunities to participate in special projects for additional compensation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;INCLUSIVE COMMUNITY&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to providing an environment of mutual respect where equitable opportunities are available to all community members without regard to race, ethnicity, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or gender expression. Archrival believes that diversity and inclusion among our partners is critical to our success as a company, and we seek to provide opportunities that allow diverse perspectives to flourish.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;We don&#39;t have your perfect role right now, but we still want to hear from you!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 600;&quot;&gt;THE ASK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please send us your resume and cover letter and we&#39;ll keep it safe until the right role pops open.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a detail-oriented Production Assistant to join our team on a part-time contract basis. As a Production Assistant, you will be responsible for coordinating and executing production processes, ensuring high-quality output, and meeting project deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE JOB: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and maintain quality standards throughout the production process, performing checks and troubleshooting issues as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with internal teams and vendor partners, to ensure smooth workflow and clear communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and support packaging, shipping and receiving efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support management of production materials and supplies, ensuring timely shipping and inventory control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of projects and production activities, documenting in the appropriate channels and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for process improvements and recommend changes to enhance efficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a valued member of the Archrival Operations Team, lending input and feedback as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE RIGHT TYPE OF PERSON: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail and commitment to quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as a part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to carry and lift packages up to 15 lbs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OTHER NEED TO KNOWS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a part-time contract position working 5-10 hours per week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role is based in Portland, OR and is required to be in office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our agency is looking for a Senior Account Manager to manage client relationships, drive strategic initiatives, and elevate creative solutions. In this role, you will serve as a trusted advisor to clients&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR IMPACT IN THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead client relationships with confidence, serving as the primary liaison and trusted strategic partner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive long-term client success by deeply understanding their brand objectives and aligning agency expertise to exceed expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide internal teams to develop creative strategies, ideas, and campaigns that push boundaries and deliver results for the client.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all work meets the highest creative and strategic standards, maintaining brand integrity and aligning with client goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the full client experience, leading kick off, presentations, and key touchpoints while proactively problem-solving challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and refine statements of work, project briefs, and client-facing materials to ensure clarity and strategic alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Account Directors on large-scale accounts, providing leadership and support in driving complex initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead project planning and operational oversight across accounts, ensuring appropriate resourcing, realistic timelines, budget management, scope control, and seamless execution from kickoff through final delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and capitalize on growth opportunities, fostering deeper client relationships and expanding agency impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track client profitability, optimize workflows, and contribute to agency-wide process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively solve challenges, bringing forward-thinking solutions that redefine industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a pulse on emerging trends, ensuring Archrival stays ahead of shifts in the market and consumer behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU NEED TO SUCCEED:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds strong client relationships and earns trust through thoughtful communication, strategic thinking, and consistent delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understands how to connect client goals to agency solutions, balancing big-picture thinking with day-to-day execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrives in fast-paced environments, confidently navigating ambiguity, shifting priorities, and unexpected challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads with a solutions-oriented mindset, proactively identifying opportunities and solving problems before they arise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings strong presentation and communication skills, confidently leading client meetings and key conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has experience managing budgets, scopes, timelines, and resources while maintaining project health and profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborates effectively across teams to deliver great work and exceptional client experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stays curious about youth culture, consumer behavior, and emerging trends, translating insights into opportunities for clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has 5+ years of experience managing complex projects, campaigns, or programs for national and/or global brands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU AT ARCHRIVAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of youth culture and passion for continuous learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to go against the grain and take on challenges that may have never been done before&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team first, remain humble and never leave another Archrivaler hanging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driven to excellence, committed to grinding out great work mixed with a playful point-of-view&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a community of belonging, our collective
